{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πλίνθος</b>, ἡ, <br /> rarely <b>πλίνθον</b>, τό (see. below 11.1), <b>brick,</b> whether sun- or fire-baked, πλίνθοι ὀπταί [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.180, 186, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 552, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 2.4.12, compare 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus 153, “PAmh.” 2.99 (a) 9 (2nd c.AD), etc.\">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]; π. κεραμεαῖ, γήϊναι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 3.4.7, 7.8.14 (opposed to ὠμὴ π. 2nd c.AD: Pausanias Periegeta 8.8.7)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πλίνθους ἑλκύσαι, εἰρύσαι, make <b>bricks,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.179, 2.136 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὀπτᾶν bake <b>them,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 1.179 \">Refs</a>]; δόμοι πλίνθου (in <i>collective</i> sense) layers of <b>brick,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. passage],compare 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.20 (_plural_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πλίνθους ἐπιτιθέναι, of torture by <b>pressing,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 621: proverbial, π. πλύνειν,\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] of useless trouble, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Comica Adespota” 891, 2nd c.AD: Zenobius Paroemiographus 6.48; ὕδατι νίζειν θολερὰν διαειδέϊ π. 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 16.62. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>any brick-shaped body,</b> <br /><Level3><b>__II.1</b></Level3> <b>stone squared for building,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Inscriptiones Graecae 12.372.10, +others: _plural_ πλίνθα\">Refs</a>] <b>squared blocks</b> of marble, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Sardis” 7(1) No.93.3. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>ingot</b> of gold or silver, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 10.27.12, 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Cont.” 12 \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; of lead, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Dioscorides (Dioscurides) Medicus 5.88\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; metal <b>plate</b> let into a threshold, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 247i22 (Delph., 4th c.BC), “IG” 42(1).102.73 (Epid., 4th c.BC). \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <b>plinth of a column,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Milet. Ergebnisse 7.59, “Supp.epigram” 4.447.17 (Didyma, 2nd c.BC), 1st c.BC: Vitruvius Scriptor de Architectura Latinus 4.7.3. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G8820","accentedUnicode":"πλίνθος","shortDef":"a brick","mediumDef":"a brick","stepGloss":"a brick","stepTransliteration":"plinthos","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}